==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Neanderthal man
<hw>Neanderthal man</hw>, a species of
extinct robust humans, believed to have been widespread in the Middle
Paleolithic in Europe and western Asia; <as>as, a <ex>Neanderthal</ex>
skull</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> Neanderthalian.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source> + <source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Similar to or reminiscent of a neanderthal human;
troglodytic; primitive and uncultured.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Neanderthal</ent>⟦br⟧
